00:18:24.250 --> 00:18:27.340
But I'm curious from
the financial angle,

00:18:27.340 --> 00:18:28.767
what kind of unique problems--

00:18:28.767 --> 00:18:30.850
I imagine there are some--
that GiveDirectly deals

00:18:30.850 --> 00:18:33.270
with that you're exposed to?

00:18:33.270 --> 00:18:35.351
JOE HUSTON: Yeah.

00:18:35.351 --> 00:18:37.950
In a lot of ways,
it's focusing to just

00:18:37.950 --> 00:18:41.580
be able to spend most of your
time on the cash pipeline.

00:18:41.580 --> 00:18:43.470
And so on the
finance side, my job

00:18:43.470 --> 00:18:47.330
is to manage that entire
pipeline from donor

00:18:47.330 --> 00:18:50.910
to the first bank it hits in
the US to the foreign exchange

00:18:50.910 --> 00:18:54.320
transaction to get to Kenyan
shillings or Rwandan francs,

00:18:54.320 --> 00:18:57.086
the bank it sits there, and then
the getting to the mobile money

00:18:57.086 --> 00:18:58.710
provider and to the
eventual recipient.

00:18:58.710 --> 00:19:00.930
And so the problems
there are to first,

00:19:00.930 --> 00:19:04.080
make sure that that pipeline
is as short as possible,

00:19:04.080 --> 00:19:06.840
that money moves through the
system incredibly quickly.

00:19:06.840 --> 00:19:08.820
And so problems we're
sort of working on

00:19:08.820 --> 00:19:11.160
within that domain
are things like how

00:19:11.160 --> 00:19:13.920
do we project donations
that we can keep field

00:19:13.920 --> 00:19:16.310
operations running basically
just behind them so

00:19:16.310 --> 00:19:18.600
that the lag is very small?

00:19:18.600 --> 00:19:21.095
Second, how do we manage
that cash prudently,

00:19:21.095 --> 00:19:23.220
make sure we're getting an
interest where we should

00:19:23.220 --> 00:19:24.455
and things like that?

00:19:24.455 --> 00:19:25.830
And then third,
making sure we're

00:19:25.830 --> 00:19:28.740
managing fraud, on
the internal side

00:19:28.740 --> 00:19:31.097
with staff and things
like that and externally

00:19:31.097 --> 00:19:33.180
with mobile money providers,
with local government

00:19:33.180 --> 00:19:34.054
and things like that.

00:19:34.054 --> 00:19:35.940
And so the integrity
of the pipeline

00:19:35.940 --> 00:19:38.400
is something I spend a
lot of time on as well.

00:19:38.400 --> 00:19:39.580
