00:21:58.284 --> 00:22:00.450
SPEAKER 1: We can read from
the first Dory question.

00:22:00.450 --> 00:22:02.640
So what are the best
reasons, in your view,

00:22:02.640 --> 00:22:06.840
to be skeptical about basic
income projects or policies?

00:22:06.840 --> 00:22:10.050
JOE HUSTON: Yeah, I think my
biggest one, especially as it

00:22:10.050 --> 00:22:11.970
applies to the US
or other places

00:22:11.970 --> 00:22:15.210
where basic income
feels politically far,

00:22:15.210 --> 00:22:19.700
is that a UBI doesn't feel like
a particularly useful North

00:22:19.700 --> 00:22:20.640
Star.

00:22:20.640 --> 00:22:25.050
That there is this sort of sense
of a UBI as this Utopic policy.

00:22:25.050 --> 00:22:28.420
And because of its
elegance or simplicity,

00:22:28.420 --> 00:22:31.160
there's a very good sense of
what it should look like--

00:22:31.160 --> 00:22:32.760
that it should be universal.

00:22:32.760 --> 00:22:35.800
It should be basic, which you
could debate the exact number,

00:22:35.800 --> 00:22:39.860
but it's supposed to
meet the basic needs.

00:22:39.860 --> 00:22:43.140
And so I think almost because
it has this clear template

00:22:43.140 --> 00:22:46.350
for what you should
