00:42:05.120 --> 00:42:06.311
or things like that.

00:42:06.311 --> 00:42:08.060
It seems like that
presents an opportunity

00:42:08.060 --> 00:42:11.210
for financial institutions
or other changes.

00:42:11.210 --> 00:42:12.710
So curious to your
thoughts on that.

00:42:12.710 --> 00:42:13.700
JOE HUSTON: Yeah.

00:42:13.700 --> 00:42:17.230
And so the quick slightly long
explanation of what this is

00:42:17.230 --> 00:42:19.820
is in this UBI pilot village
where people were receiving

00:42:19.820 --> 00:42:22.370
basic income payments, a
thing people wanted to do

00:42:22.370 --> 00:42:24.290
was purchase big
things, bigger than what

00:42:24.290 --> 00:42:25.790
their monthly check was.

00:42:25.790 --> 00:42:27.650
And so they formed
different types of groups

00:42:27.650 --> 00:42:30.890
within the village and basically
made a ledger of each person

00:42:30.890 --> 00:42:32.450
every month contributes
some portion

00:42:32.450 --> 00:42:34.040
of their basic income payment.

00:42:34.040 --> 00:42:37.132
And one person every month
receives all of those payments.

00:42:37.132 --> 00:42:38.840
And so it's a way to
convert those stream

00:42:38.840 --> 00:42:44.030
payments into semi-recurring
lump sum ones instead.

00:42:44.030 --> 00:42:45.740
In terms of financial
institutions,

00:42:45.740 --> 00:42:48.230
I think people do have access.

00:42:48.230 --> 00:42:49.730
And so I think maybe
the opportunity

00:42:49.730 --> 00:42:51.740
is like a sales one.

00:42:51.740 --> 00:42:55.820
And so M-Pesa is the mobile
money provider in Kenya.

00:42:55.820 --> 00:42:58.190
And it has a ton of
different savings and loan

00:42:58.190 --> 00:43:00.080
